attributes.review:
ORang looked at the warped kettle in his hands and felt jumpy.

He walked over to the window and reflected on his duckly surroundings. He had always loved ugly Your backyard with its yucky, yarbelicious your mom. It was a place that encouraged his tendency to feel jumpy.

Then he saw something in the distance, or rather someone. It was the figure of Dorito . Dorito was a hungry queen with grubby elbows and greasy feet.

ORang gulped. He glanced at his own reflection. He was an arrogant, peculiar, cocoa drinker with moist elbows and squat feet. His friends saw him as a motionless, modern muppet. Once, he had even helped a putrid old man recover from a flying accident.

But not even an arrogant person who had once helped a putrid old man recover from a flying accident, was prepared for what Dorito had in store today.

The moon shone like thinking pigeons, making ORang unstable.

As ORang stepped outside and Dorito came closer, he could see the deadly glint in his eye.

"I am here because I want get blasted," Dorito bellowed, in a ruthless tone. He slammed his fist against ORang's chest, with the force of 8456 frogs. "I frigging hate you, ORang ."

ORang looked back, even more unstable and still fingering the warped kettle. "Dorito, skiddly bop do wop wop," he replied.

They looked at each other with calm feelings, like two glorious, gigantic guppies gyrating at a very forgetful dinner party, which had jazz music playing in the background and two tight-fisted uncles hopping to the beat.

ORang regarded Dorito's grubby elbows and greasy feet. He held out his hand. "Let's not fight," he whispered, gently.

"Hmph," pondered Dorito.

"Please?" begged ORang with puppy dog eyes.

Dorito looked active, his body blushing like a smoggy, slow sausage.

Then Dorito came inside for a nice mug of cocoa.
